---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Engage - Summer 2026"
  description="Select governance, architecture, and audit engagements with Erin Stanley through August 31, 2026. Public pricing. Bounded window."
>
  <div class="hero">
    <p class="recognition">Erin Stanley, Evoked - Engagement Window</p>
    <h1>The August deadline is not the EU AI Act. It is the day this window closes.</h1>
    <p class="tagline">
      Three engagements. Public pricing. Available through August 31, 2026.
      Then the chapter ends and a different one begins.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="container">
    <p>
      Your agents shipped. The audit room is asking a different question than the
      product room asked. Not what the agents can do. What they should refuse, who
      decides, and where that decision is written down. Most teams cannot answer
      that yet. You have weeks, not quarters, to find out whether you can.
    </p>
    <p>
      I have a bounded summer window for three kinds of work. Public rates. No
      discovery dance. If the offer matches what you need, the math is already on
      the page.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>The Three Offers</h2>

    <div class="offer-stack">

      <div class="offer-card">
        <div class="offer-head">
          <span class="offer-tag">Audit + roadmap</span>
          <span class="offer-price">$25,000</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Sovereignty Assessment</h3>
        <p class="offer-window">Four weeks. Two working sessions. Written deliverable.</p>
        <p>
          The 47-point assessment applied to your agent system across seven domains -
          identity, memory, restraint, voice, drift, refusal architecture, and governance
          surface. Findings come prioritized with a remediation roadmap your team can
          execute against. You learn where your agents hold and where they break before
          your auditors do.
        </p>
        <ul class="offer-deliverables">
          <li>Written sovereignty assessment scored against 47 properties</li>
          <li>Prioritized remediation roadmap with effort sizing</li>
          <li>One executive readout. One working session with the build team.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="offer-card">
        <div class="offer-head">
          <span class="offer-tag">Spec authoring</span>
          <span class="offer-price">$10,000</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Agent Architecture Spec</h3>
        <p class="offer-window">Two to three weeks. One working session. Written spec.</p>
        <p>
          A specification document your autonomous agents can execute against over
          long time horizons. Covers identity boundaries, memory architecture, refusal
          rights, voice discipline, and drift detection. Written in language a build
          team can ship from and an audit team can verify against. The difference
          between a demo and a deployment.
        </p>
        <ul class="offer-deliverables">
          <li>Written agent architecture specification</li>
          <li>Refusal specification authored against your operational risk surface</li>
          <li>One working session to align the build team on the spec</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="offer-card">
        <div class="offer-head">
          <span class="offer-tag">Fractional advisor</span>
          <span class="offer-price">$15,000/month</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Governance Advisor Retainer</h3>
        <p class="offer-window">Sixteen hours per month. Through August 31. Renewable.</p>
        <p>
          Standing governance counsel for teams whose agents are shipping faster than
          their guardrails. Weekly office hours, async review of build artifacts,
          executive briefings, and direct authorship on policy documents when the
          situation calls for it. Two retainer slots available for the summer window.
        </p>
        <ul class="offer-deliverables">
          <li>Weekly thirty-minute office hours with the build or governance lead</li>
          <li>Async review of refusal specs, system prompts, audit artifacts</li>
          <li>One executive briefing per month, on request</li>
          <li>Renewable September 1 at a different rate and cadence</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Why August 31</h2>
    <p>
      A 2026 governance window is not abstract. The EU AI Act high-risk obligations
      land August 2. The Anthropic-Blackstone joint venture launched a $1.5 billion
      Claude services build in May. The mid-market Claude consulting space is being
      capitalized in real time. The teams that get audit-ready this summer are not
      the teams that will get audit-ready in October. They are different teams.
    </p>
    <p>
      The window is also mine. School resumes in the fall. The work in September
      looks different than the work in July. The August 31 date is not a marketing
      hook. It is when this offer page comes down.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Why Me</h2>
    <div class="proof-bar">
      <div class="proof-item">
        <h4>Patent</h4>
        <p>Inventor on active filings in AI agent governance.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="proof-item">
        <h4>Operator</h4>
        <p>142-agent governance system in daily operation. Built, not theorized.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="proof-item">
        <h4>Author</h4>
        <p>
          Sovereignty Assessment, Trust Architecture, Restraint Specification,
          Memory Architecture, Governance Starter Kit. All published. All used.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="proof-item">
        <h4>Policy</h4>
        <p>Active engagement with NIST on AI agent identity standards.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Start the Conversation</h2>
    <p>
      If one of the three offers matches what you need, the next step is a
      thirty-minute scoping call. Public rates apply. No proposal cycle.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a href="/consulting-intake" class="btn">Engagement intake</a>
      <a href="https://cal.com/cal.com-evoked/discovery-call" class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a 30-min call</a>
      <a href="/consulting" class="btn btn-secondary">See the full service menu</a>
    </div>
    <p class="footnote">
      Two retainer slots. Limited audit slots. Architecture spec capacity scoped per week.
      Slots fill in the order they are booked.
    </p>
    <p class="footnote">
      Smaller engagements and self-serve tools - from $49 framework kits to $5,000 governance audits - live at <a href="/consulting">/consulting</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="closing">
      <p>
        The agents are not going to stop shipping. The audit room is not going to
        stop asking. The window is what it is. If this is the summer you make your
        agents legible to the people who will judge them, we should talk.
      </p>
      <p class="signature">Erin Stanley, Evoked</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    text-align: left;
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-lg) 0 var(--space-md);
  }
  .recognition {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2.4rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  .tagline {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .offer-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }
  .offer-card {
    padding: var(--space-md);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 8px;
    transition: border-color var(--transition-smooth);
  }
  .offer-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent-warm);
  }
  .offer-head {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }
  .offer-tag {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
  }
  .offer-price {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .offer-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-xs);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
  }
  .offer-window {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }
  .offer-deliverables {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .offer-deliverables li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .proof-bar {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }
  .proof-item h4 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }
  .proof-item p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }
  .btn-secondary {
    border: 1px solid var(--border-accent);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  .btn-secondary:hover {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    border-color: var(--accent-warm);
  }
  .footnote {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .closing {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .closing p {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .signature {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 1.9rem;
    }
    .offer-head {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }
</style>
